    {
        "content": "<p>Honestly, I feel like the Beta special function definition should be rewritten with MeasureTheory.integral (bochner) instead of interval. Yes, it would make my life a lot easier, but on top of this, Gamma function uses this type as well</p>",
        "id": 469777824,
        "sender_full_name": "Alvan Arulandu",
        "timestamp": 1726174122
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Plus, the Beta.lean isn't being used by any other part of mathlib so I feel like this is safe</p>",
        "id": 469777905,
        "sender_full_name": "Alvan Arulandu",
        "timestamp": 1726174155
    },
    {
